1
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:29,800
Although the killer cleaned the scene,

2
00:01:30,039 --> 00:01:32,770
there are still some residual bloodstains here.

3
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:33,720
That's right.

4
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:35,560
This is the primary crime scene.

5
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:41,650
Qiu Chen.

6
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:44,840
The fingerprints on the school warehouse's fire alarm,

7
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,440
how is the comparison going?

8
00:01:47,039 --> 00:01:48,240
Here are the results.

9
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,259
Whose are they?

10
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:51,500
I'm asking you.

11
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:52,810
No need to check.

12
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,650
Wh-what do you mean?

13
00:01:57,039 --> 00:01:58,240
These fingerprints,

14
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,170
are mine.

15
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,400
Someone put my fingerprints

16
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,400
on the fire alarm.

17
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:20,960
*Sigh.*

18
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,400
The fingerprint

19
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,000
comparison results are out.

20
00:02:24,079 --> 00:02:24,880
It's Qiu Chen.

21
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:27,920
How

22
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:29,840
is this possible?

23
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,079
Who is so capable

24
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:35,000
as to steal his fingerprints right under Qiu Chen's nose

25
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,460
and then

26
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:37,340
put them on the fire alarm?

27
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,520
The exchange of husbands murder,

28
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,880
the green gauze tent case,

29
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:57,560
and the bullying revenge case.

30
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,120
The killers in these cases

31
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:01,080
were all once victims.

32
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,200
They committed the crimes

33
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,600
both to take revenge on their former abusers

34
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:08,680
and to expose those people's sins,

35
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:11,420
proving they got what they deserved.

36
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:15,720
The killers act as judges.

37
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:19,810
This is very similar to the Scavenger from back then.

38
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,400
The difference is that

39
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,680
the original Scavenger committed the crimes himself.

40
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,880
The current killer

41
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:28,000
is manipulating from behind the scenes.

42
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,800
Not only have the criminal methods upgraded,

43
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,160
but

44
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:32,180
it's also harder to track him.

45
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:37,120
He's no longer satisfied with manipulating from behind.

46
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:39,650
Helping the perpetrators erase their tracks

47
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:42,900
seems to give him more of a sense of accomplishment.

48
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,460
He has been guiding us,

49
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:48,079
making us believe in his existence.

50
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,490
So he didn't hide at all,

51
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:52,290
but instead came out into the open.

52
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,060
Because he is very confident,

53
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:56,250
confident that he won't be caught.

54
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:59,410
So we don't need to look for that mark anymore.

55
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:00,130
Exactly,

56
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,850
because he has stepped in himself.

57
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:04,850
Oh, Chief Zhang.

58
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,480
This is obviously a trap.

59
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,450
Can't you see it?

60
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:10,970
The killer just wants to throw our investigation off track.

61
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,040
I trust you

62
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,240
and Qiu Chen.

63
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:14,040
But

64
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:16,450
discipline is discipline.

65
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:19,760
Until the fingerprint issue is cleared up,

66
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,320
Qiu Chen must step aside.

67
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,530
This is the rule.

68
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,410
Rules are rigid.

69
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,400
But people...

70
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,000
Yuming.

71
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:28,850
Rules are our principle

72
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,210
and our bottom line.

73
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,640
I trust Qiu Chen

74
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:34,200
and everyone in the Criminal Investigation Brigade.

75
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:34,480
So,

76
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,360
you must solve the case as soon as possible,

77
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,290
find the killer,

78
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,600
and uncover the truth.

79
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,320
Only in this way

80
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,120
can you verify

81
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,180
all your previous speculations.

82
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,010
Understood.

83
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:58,640
Qiu Chen.

84
00:04:58,640 --> 00:04:59,370
Chief Zhang.

85
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,040
You want to look at

86
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:03,240
the files on the Scavenger case, right?

87
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:04,040
Yes.

88
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,800
But according to the rules,

89
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,360
you can't enter the archives

90
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,090
or consult any files right now.

91
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:10,440
Director Zhang.

92
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,200
But other than investigating cases,

93
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,730
I don't know what else to do.

94
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,240
When Gu Yuming was suspended from duty,

95
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,400
he said exactly the same thing

96
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,600
as you're saying now.

97
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,330
Don't worry.

98
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:22,770
Come with me.

99
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:39,770
Feeling better?

100
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:45,840
Chief Zhang told me today

101
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,000
that in the Scavenger serial cases,

102
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,800
your fingerprints were also found

103
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,260
at one of the crime scenes.

104
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,360
You were also asked to be suspended

105
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,960
and recuse yourself from the case.

106
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:58,520
You were even punished for acting without authorization.

107
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,050
Chief Zhang has a big mouth.

108
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,760
He tells you everything.

109
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,480
So I completely understand you.

110
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,040
But

111
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,720
rules are rules.

112
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:10,810
I understand why Chief Zhang told me this.

113
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:13,080
To remind me to follow the rules.

114
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:15,650
But it made me think of something else.

115
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:16,640
What is it?

116
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:21,160
I remembered that the Scavenger case files mentioned

117
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,440
that you stated

118
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:25,200
you went to the scene with my dad.

119
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,540
That's what I thought too.

120
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,640
So I've always blamed you

121
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,530
for not protecting him.

122
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,610
But I found another suspicious point.

123
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,500
What else did you find?

124
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,640
My dad was a very principled man.

125
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,380
Knowing his personality,

126
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,620
since you were suspended at the time,

127
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,920
he couldn't have taken you to the scene.

128
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:48,560
So I assume

129
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,440
he must have gone to the scene alone,

130
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:53,810
and you secretly followed him.

131
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:56,540
Unfortunately, you were a step too late.

132
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,640
If you really read that file,

133
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:01,440
you would know

134
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,520
that I went with your dad.

135
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,080
You said in that file

136
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,480
that my dad ran over first

137
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,330
to fight the Scavenger.

138
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,560
But what you don't know is

139
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,320
his Achilles tendinitis acted up that day.

140
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,580
He couldn't run at all.

141
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:17,040
You were still living on campus back then.

142
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,100
How would you know?

143
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,880
I checked the medication records with the team doctor.

144
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,480
The day before the incident,

145
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:27,320
he had just picked up medicine for Achilles tendinitis,

146
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,120
celecoxib.

147
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:33,920
That's right.

148
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:37,240
The morning Master had his accident,

149
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:39,240
my suspension had just been lifted.

150
00:07:40,159 --> 00:07:43,490
I really didn't know his Achilles tendinitis had flared up.

151
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:45,840
When I arrived,

152
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:48,520
he was already...

153
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,320
Hold on.

154
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,480
Grab it.

155
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:53,440
Grab it.

156
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:54,360
You must hold on.

157
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:54,820
Master.

158
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,040
I can't make it.

159
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,240
You go.

160
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,440
Hold on tight!

161
00:07:59,440 --> 00:07:59,840
Ah.

162
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,480
Master.

163
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,970
Then why didn't you tell everyone?

164
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:49,800
Master has always been cautious and strictly followed rules when handling cases.

165
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,560
But this time he went alone.

166
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,600
He was either anxious to save An Rong,

167
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,530
or the Scavenger

168
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,360
made some special requests of him.

169
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:59,020
Anyway, I believe Master must have his reasons.

170
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:02,360
But I'm worried that the public

171
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,720
will misunderstand him,

172
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:05,080
saying he was rash and greedy for credit,

173
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:07,340
and accusing him of being too impulsive.

174
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,320
So you did this

175
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:11,010
for his reputation?

176
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,040
I did break the rules.

177
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:23,040
I thank you on his behalf.

178
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,740
Compared to what my master did for me,

179
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:33,600
this is

180
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:34,930
nothing.

181
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,020
If that's the case,

182
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:39,680
that copycat

183
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:42,580
might have contacted the Scavenger.

184
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,330
It seems we have to catch him

185
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,960
to find out what my dad actually discovered back then.

186
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:49,680
Right.

187
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:52,940
The truth will eventually come to light.

188
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,300
I was careless.

189
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:04,620
I didn't expect

190
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:08,140
him to come straight for me this time.

191
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:15,720
What's wrong?

192
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,420
Feeling discouraged?

193
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,360
The Qiu Chen I know

194
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,730
would never give up easily.

195
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:28,160
Of course.

196
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,360
I'll definitely find his weak spot.

197
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,250
As for Wu Fei's case,

198
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:36,680
I'll investigate it to the very end.

199
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:38,360
Let me see.

200
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:45,480
Let's see who's making our Xiaochen so upset.

201
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:52,960
This Principal Wu Fei

202
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:56,580
seems to have Narcissistic Personality Disorder.

203
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:58,890
Narcissistic Personality Disorder?

204
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:01,290
Narcissistic Personality Disorder.

205
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:02,720
These kinds of people

206
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:05,200
are usually masters of emotional manipulation.

207
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,400
Their typical characteristics

208
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:06,800
are

209
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:07,920
exaggerating their own importance

210
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:09,250
and belittling others.

211
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:10,600
Another characteristic

212
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,320
is a lack of empathy.

213
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,440
When dealing with relationships,

214
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,960
they are selfish and cold.

215
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,220
But Wu Fei is obviously

216
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,280
a playboy and romantic.

217
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,720
Why are so many women flocking to him?

218
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,240
His hot and cold attitude

219
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:30,880
is like a drug.

220
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,120
It stimulates the brain

221
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:34,720
and makes people dependent.

222
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,360
The second reason

223
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:37,860
is that the victims

224
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,170
have childhood trauma.

225
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,080
That familiar feeling of being hurt

226
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:44,480
makes people who lack love

227
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,610
mistake it for love.

228
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:47,780
The last reason

229
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:48,680
is arrogance.

230
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,680
They always fantasize that they are the exception

231
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,410
and can change this kind of man.

232
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:02,080
Siyu.

233
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,000
Any discoveries yet?

234
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:12,160
My master is worried sick.

235
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:14,450
He hasn't slept a wink for two days.

236
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:16,840
Quiet.

237
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:18,080
Almost there.

238
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:28,960
What is this?

239
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:30,480
Hair.

240
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,080
Hair?

241
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:35,300
Hey.

242
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:36,840
I found it.

243
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:37,570
Found it?

244
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,250
In Wu Fei's respiratory tract,

245
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,380
I found residual cat hair fragments.

246
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:43,640
This means

247
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:45,400
that before he died,

248
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:46,440
Wu Fei came into contact with a cat

249
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:47,320
or a cat owner.

250
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:51,240
But I questioned

251
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,080
the women who were in contact with him.

252
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,810
They all said Wu Fei hated cats.

253
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,490
Cao Wenwen also said

254
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,200
Wu Fei was allergic to cat hair.

255
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,760
She wanted to get a cat before,

256
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:01,080
but Wu Fei warned her,

257
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:03,180
'If you get a cat, we're done.'

258
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:05,760
He really thought of himself as an emperor.

259
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:06,560
Whether to get a cat or not

260
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:08,880
was his obedience test for his girlfriend.

261
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:09,320
Yeah.

262
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:12,210
Wait.

263
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:12,960
No.

264
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:16,800
If he didn't come into contact with cat owners or cats,

265
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:19,240
then this hair very likely came from the killer.

266
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,520
Hey, you're right.

267
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,260
I'll go check his social connections now

268
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,120
to see if any of them own a cat.

269
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:26,740
Go quickly.

270
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:43,530
Hello, Siyu.

271
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:44,450
Qiu Chen.

272
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:47,600
According to regulations, I shouldn't tell you this.

273
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,520
But I think you'd want to know.

274
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,040
Did you find something new on Wu Fei's body?

275
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:54,970
Tell me quickly.

276
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:56,480
Let's put it this way.

277
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:58,920
I found cat hair in the victim's respiratory tract.

278
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:00,180
But he didn't own a cat.

279
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:02,880
And none of the women he recently dated owned one either.

280
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,410
You know what I mean, right?

281
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,180
Be careful.

282
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:10,520
Thank you.

283
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:11,250
Give it to me.

284
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:24,560
Siyu.

285
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:27,000
Someone around Wu Fei really does keep a cat.
